FBIS4-48190 "drafr094_a_94016" FBIS-AFR-94-094 Daily Report 15 May 1994 CENTRAL AFRICA Rwanda RPF Reports on Further Gains RPF Reports on Further Gains EA1505203094 (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura in Kinyarwanda to Rwanda 1730 GMT 15 May 94 EA1505203094 (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura Kinyarwanda BFN [Excerpt] The Rwanda Patriotic Front [RPF] forces control the entire Byumba Prefecture, the entire Prefecture of Kibungo, about three quarters of of the Kigali Prefecture, and it controls half the Ruhengeri Prefecture. This is the part of the country that has already been snatched from the clique of leaders and their stooges: the presidential guards, the [Coalition for the defense of the republic militia, [Interahamwe], and the Revolutionary National Movement for Democracy and Development militia, Impuzamugambi. As for the rest of the country, it will not take long. Let them be strong. As for Kigali town, the rebels control northern, eastern, and southeastern parts. Fighting is taking place around Ruhengeri. In the south of the country, fighting took place in the southern part of Bugesera and now the military barracks of the region has fallen to the rebels who now control it. [passage omitted]
